  title="Privacy Policy – Roster App"
  description="Privacy policy for the Roster iOS app. Local-first, no tracking, no backend. Last updated: 23 June 2026.">

  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="updated">Last updated: 23 June 2026</p>

  <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Elias Wilkening</strong><br />
    c/o Impressumservice Dein-Impressum · Stettiner Str. 41 · 35410 Hungen · Germany<br />
    Email: <a href="mailto:support@rosterapp.tech">support@rosterapp.tech</a> ·
    Phone: <a href="tel:+4915225393437">+49 152 25393437</a>
  </p>

  <h2>2. Core principle: local processing</h2>
  <p>Roster is a fully local app. All content you enter — including people, notes, reflections, health check-ins, agreements, photos and settings — is stored exclusively on your device. There is <strong>no</strong> Roster server, no cloud storage by us, and no transmission of your content to third parties. No tracking, no analytics, no ad networks.</p>

  <h2>3. What data is processed?</h2>

  <h3>3.1 Locally on your device (entered by you)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Profile: name, pronouns, optional profile photo</li>
    <li>Connections: name, relationship type, pronouns, optional photo, notes, agreements, milestones, health data, burn-after-read notes, mood entries</li>
    <li>Reflections / journal entries</li>
    <li>App settings (e.g. tone, reminders)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3.2 Data processed by Apple</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>App Store / StoreKit:</strong> Apple processes your Apple ID and payment data for subscriptions. We receive only anonymised confirmation of whether a valid subscription exists.</li>
    <li><strong>Local notifications:</strong> Reminders are triggered locally by Apple's system — no server transmission.</li>
    <li><strong>PhotosPicker:</strong> Access only to the photo you select, not your entire library. Stored locally in the app.</li>
    <li><strong>AVSpeech (optional):</strong> On-device speech synthesis — no cloud transmission.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3.3 Data we do not collect</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Location data · Contacts / address book · Microphone recordings · Advertising IDs (IDFA) · Crash or performance telemetry</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Legal bases</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR — contract performance</li>
    <li>Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR — legitimate interests (secure, stable app)</li>
    <li>Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR — consent (e.g. notifications, photo access)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Retention</h2>
  <p>Your data remains on your device for as long as the app is installed. Upon uninstallation, all locally stored data is removed by the operating system. Burn-after-read notes delete automatically after your chosen lifetime (1 hour to 1 month).</p>

  <h2>6. Third-party sharing</h2>
  <p>No sharing of your app content with third parties. No transfer to third countries.</p>

  <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
  <p>You have rights under Art. 15–22 GDPR: access, rectification, erasure, restriction, data portability and objection. Since all data is on your device, you can exercise these rights directly in the app. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority (Art. 77 GDPR).</p>

  <h2>8. Security</h2>
  <p>Roster stores data in the app sandbox using iOS device encryption (Data Protection). We recommend securing your device with a passcode, Face ID or Touch ID.</p>

  <h2>9. Contact &amp; changes</h2>
  <p>Questions: <a href="mailto:support@rosterapp.tech">support@rosterapp.tech</a>. The current version is always available at <a href="https://rosterapp.tech/appinfo/datenschutzrichtlinie">rosterapp.tech/appinfo/datenschutzrichtlinie</a>.</p>

</AppInfoLayout>
